<h1>Problem 1685 - 2014 USAMO, P2 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(\mathbb{Z}\) be the set of integers. Find all functions \(f : \mathbb{Z} \rightarrow \mathbb{Z}\) such that \[xf(2f(y)-x)+y^2f(2x-f(y))=\frac{f(x)^2}{x}+f(yf(y))\] for all \(x, y \in \mathbb{Z}\) with \(x \neq 0\).</p>
